snippet: Ms. Mounsey put such a stamp on roles — even ones she did not create — that people still recall her delivery of certain moments after more than 50 years.
abstract: Yvonne Mounsey, dancer who created roles for the New York City Ballet, dies at age 93.
lead_paragraph: Ms. Mounsey put such a stamp on roles — even ones she did not create — that people still recall her delivery of certain moments after more than 50 years.

headline.seo: Yvonne Mounsey, City Ballet Dancer and a Teacher, Dies at 93

headline.print_headline: Yvonne Mounsey Dies at 93; Created Roles for City Ballet
